Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery bowl; interior glazed dark brown with added red band lined in white on wall; outside in part glazed, but much worn; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.367)
